        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-30 17:28:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nWhile this looks ok and matches past fixes for Coverity complaints, I am curious why only these instances of these calls generate errors.  Looks like there are many more similar calls elsewhere in the code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
